	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The AY-3-8912 should be electrically identical to the AY-3-8910. It's the same part with all the I/O pins chopped out.<br /><br />There might be some differences on how the part is enabled as well since as the AY-3-8910 original purpose was being the sound chip on GI's videogame system (the INTL) and because of that it has a odd set of enable pins.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


