	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Just commenting, yet again: <br /><br />There's no need to reset the AY chip. <br />It's so dumb (simple) it works without a initial clear pulse. The DATASHEET even mentions that RESET pin has a built in pullup resistor, meaning I could leave it disconnected if I wanted to...<br /><br />I have both the AY and YM chips on my carts RESET pin tied to +5V and both work perfectly.  <br /><br />Holding RESET removes the clock so the chip does not play any sound while the system is reset...

		

		</td>
	</tr>
